Dingleberries are peices of feces lodged to the hair or fur around the anus, and cannont reach the surface of the toilet water by methods such as shakeing, rocking or pinching off.  Once they are attached there are called grogans, and must be removed with sissors or a washcloth.  They can prove to be quite a challange to the owners of Persian cats or humans who do not bathe often enough.